WEBVTT

00:06.440 --> 00:11.011
1953 was a year
of all-American values.

00:11.011 --> 00:14.282
**

00:14.282 --> 00:16.984
"I Love Lucy" was
the number one show

00:16.984 --> 00:19.520
on television.

00:19.520 --> 00:21.389
Dwight Eisenhower
was sworn in

00:21.389 --> 00:23.757
as the country's
34th President.

00:23.757 --> 00:26.460
**

00:26.460 --> 00:29.063
And suburban culture
was a way of life.

00:29.063 --> 00:31.665
**

00:31.665 --> 00:33.301
But under the surface,

00:33.301 --> 00:36.570
society was
as repressed as ever.

00:36.570 --> 00:40.841
It was a very culturally
and sexually conservative time.

00:40.841 --> 00:42.243
**

00:42.243 --> 00:45.679
Men and women were
expected to go to college,

00:45.679 --> 00:49.550
get a job, get married,
settle down, and raise a family.

00:49.550 --> 00:52.386
It was the new American dream,

00:52.386 --> 00:54.788
the white picket fence
out in the suburbs.

00:54.788 --> 00:57.791
And that's exactly the life
that Hefner was living,

00:57.791 --> 01:02.296
but he found it deeply
unsatisfying and boring.

01:02.296 --> 01:06.567
It was clear to me
that America needed a change,

01:06.567 --> 01:09.270
so I decided I was going
to create a magazine

01:09.270 --> 01:11.705
that would challenge
conformity.

01:11.705 --> 01:14.508
**

01:14.508 --> 01:17.945
A modern men's magazine
about lifestyle,

01:17.945 --> 01:22.082
art, culture, and sex,

01:22.082 --> 01:25.686
and I'd call it Stag Party.

01:25.686 --> 01:28.922
But I knew the first issue
needed the perfect cover girl,

01:28.922 --> 01:35.095
and after months of searching,
I had finally found her.

01:42.770 --> 01:47.741
Hey, Hef, I got some more
girls here for you.

01:47.741 --> 01:49.677
- What do you think about that?
- Good.

01:49.677 --> 01:56.150
I have an option myself.
What do you think of
this?

02:03.056 --> 02:07.395
Um... that's Marilyn Monroe.

02:07.395 --> 02:11.899
That's her.
She's our pin-up girl.

02:14.568 --> 02:16.770
In the spring of 1953,

02:16.770 --> 02:19.573
I bought the rights
to nude photos

02:19.573 --> 02:23.311
of one of the most famous
women in the world,

02:23.311 --> 02:25.846
Marilyn Monroe.

02:25.846 --> 02:28.649
**

02:28.649 --> 02:32.653
Now that we had our model,
I worked around the clock,

02:32.653 --> 02:36.324
creating every single aspect
of the magazine...

02:36.324 --> 02:38.592
**

02:38.592 --> 02:44.432
...what would be in it,
how it would look.

02:44.432 --> 02:47.501
He put the first issue out
singlehandedly.

02:47.501 --> 02:50.170
He went over
all the material,

02:50.170 --> 02:52.906
he did some of
the drawings himself.

02:52.906 --> 02:56.944
I was determined to create
the perfect first issue.

02:56.944 --> 02:59.747
There was a section
with party jokes,

02:59.747 --> 03:03.116
another on designs
for the modern office.

03:03.116 --> 03:06.654
We would even publish
classic literature

03:06.654 --> 03:08.389
from some of the most
well known authors

03:08.389 --> 03:11.091
in the world.

03:11.091 --> 03:14.928
The boldest thing Hef
did with the magazine

03:14.928 --> 03:19.032
is that he really
dismantled the idea

03:19.032 --> 03:21.835
of the 1950s masculinity.

03:21.835 --> 03:24.405
In the first issue,
in the editor's letter,

03:24.405 --> 03:27.575
Hef very plainly says,
other men's magazines

03:27.575 --> 03:30.077
focus on hunting
and fishing and sports.

03:30.077 --> 03:31.745
We're not doing any of that.

03:31.745 --> 03:36.450
We're gonna talk about jazz
and cocktails and Picasso.

03:36.450 --> 03:41.789
We'd talk about culture,
but we'd also focus on sex.

03:41.789 --> 03:44.858
**

03:44.858 --> 03:46.827
When people raised questions

03:46.827 --> 03:49.597
about why we included sex
in the magazine,

03:49.597 --> 03:52.165
my response always was,
how could you put together

03:52.165 --> 03:54.067
a men's magazine
and not include

03:54.067 --> 03:56.136
the primary thing
that men are interested in?

03:56.136 --> 04:00.207
The whole idea from the
beginning was to incorporate sex

04:00.207 --> 04:04.745
as one, normal and logical and
healthy part of a total package

04:04.745 --> 04:07.781
that appealed
to a male audience.

04:07.781 --> 04:12.252
We featured articles on modern
dating and married life...

04:12.252 --> 04:14.422
**

04:14.422 --> 04:16.524
and instructions
for how to play

04:16.524 --> 04:18.526
a provocative new party game

04:18.526 --> 04:21.962
called "Strip Quiz."

04:21.962 --> 04:24.332
**

04:24.332 --> 04:28.802
I think that we have it very,
very engrained in our heads

04:28.802 --> 04:31.939
to be very uncomfortable
with sex,

04:31.939 --> 04:33.941
but that's the reason
I'm here.

04:33.941 --> 04:35.443
That's the reason
why you're here.

04:35.443 --> 04:37.878
That's the reason why
we're all here.

04:37.878 --> 04:40.714
My hope was that my magazine

04:40.714 --> 04:44.852
would bring sex
to the mainstream.

04:44.852 --> 04:47.721
**

04:57.465 --> 05:01.802
But just as we were putting the
final touches on the magazine,

05:01.802 --> 05:04.505
everything came
to a standstill.

05:08.208 --> 05:10.478
It turns out,
there was a hunting magazine

05:10.478 --> 05:13.046
already on the market
called Stag,

05:13.046 --> 05:17.451
and as soon as Stag
got wind of Stag Party,

05:17.451 --> 05:21.655
they threatened to sue us
for copyright infringement.

05:21.655 --> 05:26.527
Now, with only a week
before our deadline,

05:26.527 --> 05:29.363
we had to completely
re-edit the magazine

05:29.363 --> 05:33.434
and come up
with a brand new title.

05:35.803 --> 05:39.673
