05:39.673 --> 05:43.611
* Every little thing
you do *

05:43.611 --> 05:46.346
* Is it sleight of hand *

05:46.346 --> 05:51.619
* That commands my heart
to love you? *

05:51.619 --> 05:55.623
* Every little movement *

05:55.623 --> 05:59.693
* Every
little movement **

06:08.001 --> 06:12.105
Facing a potential lawsuit,
I gathered my staff

06:12.105 --> 06:16.577
to try and come up with
a new name for the magazine.

06:16.577 --> 06:17.778
Bachelor.

06:17.778 --> 06:18.879
Ah, it makes it sound

06:18.879 --> 06:20.213
like we're not
for married men.

06:20.213 --> 06:21.949
We'd be cutting out
a whole reader base.

06:21.949 --> 06:25.419
What about something
like Sir or Gentlemen?

06:25.419 --> 06:26.720
No, no, it's too literal.

06:26.720 --> 06:29.156
It has to be fun.
What does the nameJaguar

06:29.156 --> 06:30.323
have to do
with a car company?

06:30.323 --> 06:32.560
Nothing, but it
sounds cool, right?

06:32.560 --> 06:35.663
Oh, oh! What was the name
of that car company

06:35.663 --> 06:40.100
my mom used to work for?
Playboy.

06:42.870 --> 06:45.038
Playboy.

06:45.038 --> 06:48.308
**

06:48.308 --> 06:53.180
We spent many, many hours
talking about names.

06:53.180 --> 06:54.848
Finally, I remembered
that my mother

06:54.848 --> 06:58.285
had worked for an
automobile company in Detroit

06:58.285 --> 07:00.688
called Playboy Automobile,

07:00.688 --> 07:03.691
and it was a very
sporty looking automobile,

07:03.691 --> 07:06.226
a nice looking automobile,
and that's what made me

07:06.226 --> 07:09.530
mention Playboy
as a possibility.

07:09.530 --> 07:12.700
Playboy. Perfect.

07:12.700 --> 07:16.069
It isn't aggressive.
It isn't hyper-masculine.

07:16.069 --> 07:18.706
Yeah, okay, you're doing
nudie magazines,

07:18.706 --> 07:21.174
but there's
a sophistication to it.

07:21.174 --> 07:22.710
**

07:22.710 --> 07:25.613
We had our new name.

07:25.613 --> 07:28.181
Now we had to quickly
revise the cover

07:28.181 --> 07:30.618
and remove all references
to Stag Party

07:30.618 --> 07:32.886
throughout the magazine.

07:32.886 --> 07:38.959
Back then, when you're literally
pasting print onto a page,

07:38.959 --> 07:41.695
somebody would have to take
a knife, a little X-Acto knife,

07:41.695 --> 07:46.900
and cut out every Stag Party
on every page of the magazine

07:46.900 --> 07:49.737
and replace it with Playboy.
Even today,

07:49.737 --> 07:51.839
with desktop publishing
and all that kind of stuff,

07:51.839 --> 07:55.175
that would be an
incredible amount of work.

07:55.175 --> 07:57.978
**

07:57.978 --> 08:00.413
Even our cartoon mascot
of a deer

08:00.413 --> 08:03.316
would have to change
to something else,

08:03.316 --> 08:05.519
and we chose a bunny.

08:05.519 --> 08:06.854
**

08:06.854 --> 08:09.523
The rabbit captures
the sophistication,

08:09.523 --> 08:11.859
the silliness of the brand.

08:11.859 --> 08:15.596
There is the sort of sexual
connotation of a rabbit

08:15.596 --> 08:17.798
that comes through.

08:17.798 --> 08:22.469
I had no idea at the time,
but that one little change

08:22.469 --> 08:26.039
would come to define
the magazine for decades.

08:26.039 --> 08:28.475
We had our mascot in place,

08:28.475 --> 08:33.446
and with Marilyn on the cover,
we were ready to go.

08:33.446 --> 08:35.082
**

08:35.082 --> 08:38.351
Soon, almost 70,000 copies
of Playboy

08:38.351 --> 08:42.455
would be heading to major
cities across the country.

08:42.455 --> 08:44.825
**

08:44.825 --> 08:48.562
The only question was,
would it sell?

08:48.562 --> 08:51.098
**

08:56.069 --> 09:01.208
In December of 1953,
my magazine hit the newsstands.

09:01.208 --> 09:02.976
Thank you.

09:05.679 --> 09:11.051
Hef got up and lurked
around newsstands in Chicago

09:11.051 --> 09:14.021
and waited to see if anyone
would pick up the copy

09:14.021 --> 09:16.824
and has talked about
how excited he was

09:16.824 --> 09:18.826
the first time
he saw someone buy it.

09:18.826 --> 09:22.996
And I imagine he was
elated to know

09:22.996 --> 09:25.298
there were other people out
there who felt like he did,

09:25.298 --> 09:28.902
because he was taking
this gamble.

09:31.471 --> 09:36.076
I was excited,
but I was also nervous,

09:36.076 --> 09:39.412
so nervous I didn't put
my name or issue number

09:39.412 --> 09:41.615
on our first publication.

09:41.615 --> 09:44.484
**

09:44.484 --> 09:46.219
I felt at the time, even if
there was never going to be

09:46.219 --> 09:49.657
another issue that
I'd had my chance, and indeed,

09:49.657 --> 09:51.759
at that point, I was not sure
there would be a second issue.

09:51.759 --> 09:53.661
That's why it
had no date on it.

09:53.661 --> 09:59.800
Whether I succeeded or not,
I'd had the chance to try.

10:01.201 --> 10:04.638
And then, the numbers came in.

10:04.638 --> 10:08.041
**

10:08.041 --> 10:10.443
In its first two weeks
on the newsstands,

10:10.443 --> 10:15.048
nearly 80% of
the 70, 000 issues we printed

10:15.048 --> 10:18.251
were sold across the country.

10:18.251 --> 10:20.353
* Don't you know
you gotta be strong? *

10:20.353 --> 10:22.890
